A vintage 1950s-style technical illustration showing two massive mainframe computers on opposite sides of a globe, connected by thick data cables that pulse with glowing energy streams. The globe shows Asia and Europe prominently, emphasizing distance. Speed lines and motion blur effects surround the cables on one side (appearing slow and sluggish with muted colors) while the other side bursts with vibrant golden light trails moving at tremendous velocity. The aesthetic evokes old IBM technical manuals with warm sepia tones, cross-hatching details, and a retro-futuristic optimism about computing power.
